The paper discusses the use of neural networks for solving real-world problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and sequential data analysis (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional software analysis techniques, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a method for extracting probabilistic models from RNNs, which could be relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
